Unlike many of you, I've been on Albion as a Friar.   He's level 29 (would be MUCH higher if I weren't a guildmaster, sheesh, it's alot of work)<br>
I also have an Armsman and a Cleric although much lower.<br>
<br>
Last night I went to Igraine and made a Stungard dorf healer.<br>
<br>
Several things I found already.<br>
<br>
I started fresh, by myself, no money, nada.<br>
<br>
By level 2(less than 3 minutes), I was covered head to toe with leather.  While it has crappy AF, it's got that absorb that works fine.<br>
<br>
By the time I was 4, I had amassed 25 silver.    When I dinged five, I was half covered in store bought(don't recall the name of the stuff), and had a decent orange hammer and I _STILL_ have about 10 silver left.<br>
<br>
This all in the space of under 45 minutes.<br>
<br>
The places I fought right around Mularn had consistant color spawns and there was plenty of prey.   There were no red or higher roamers amidst a sea of blues like there is in Camelot hills with the bandits.<br>
<br>
All the mobs seemed drop more loot than Albion and the loot they did have seemed to sell for about double similar items sell for in Albion.   I recall lots of &lt; 10 copper items off skells  and such in Albion.   The stuff around Mularn was selling for 15-30 coppers off level 2-3 mobs.   I would like to see loot drop percentages and sale value, kill for kill in all the realms.  I suspect Midgard has an edge here.<br>
<br>
My Armsman in Albion took an hour or so by himself to get to level 5.   He started with 10 gold(it took about 20 silver to completely outfit him) and even having this advantage, his funds after 5 levels hadn't even broken back over 10 gold.  He got ZERO armor drops.<br>
<br>
I've read that others have found the same thing.  Now I'm a believer.  If the trend continues, then what others have said is true; It is easier to level in Midgard.<br>
<br>
I'm going to work on this guy over the weekend and see what I end up with.  I suspect he'll get 12(where my armsman is at) much quicker as He was mowing thru stuff just using his chumpy hammer.   My cleric had it much rougher for some reason.<br>
<br>
If I can level this one like I suspect, I'm going to have renewed interest in the game(close to cancelling).  At 29 on Galahad, I'm outgrowing the crowded catacombs and I'm a bad backup healer in the barrows.   Llyn barfog has greened out and Lyonesse is hugely purple.    In the snow frontier I'm archer bait while trying to get experience and forest savauuge just sucks.  The mobs in the forest go from very grey to very purple in a hurry and they are mostly trees which really smack leather wearers around since it's not a slash attack.<br>
There is a very narrow band of things that I can fight and it's mostly in cornwall, which by the volume of people there indicates I'm not alone.  <br>
<br>
Ah well, that's my babble for the day.<br>
<br>
-Mal<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
