<br>
Your experience in Midgard is interesting, but have you considered that maybe only the starting area you chose there was better than your Albion starting locations.  I do vividly remember Campacorentin Forest sucking pretty badly as a starting location, but it got a lot better as I moved out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umalbor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malbor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druid in Absentia<br>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/28/01 10:41:33 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/malbor/malbor.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I sampled the dark side</span><hr size=1> <br>
&gt;&gt;Llyn Barfog doesn't even come close to greening out at level 29&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
Yeah, it sorta does.  The Bwgans are mostly green.  The Bwgan elders are the only thing left that's blue and they are only 20% of the population.  The hobgobs, Cythrauls(cept that one mean one) and boars are grey or green.   The Dinos(alfanc) in the water Are mostly blue, but unless you get a pristine alfanc hide, the loot sucks and besides...fighting in the water sucks.   The monks are yellow or orange, but perma camped and come in groups of 3.  If you group to kill them, you need a tank that can tank 3 and then he's not getting good exp.   There are a few rare singles, but they aren't regular fare.<br>
<br>
The Cyclops are still red/orange but only 3 of those on a slow spawn.<br>
<br>
The Bwgals are red, but where is there a consistant group of them?  I only see one on occasion and I've been around that whole area many times.<br>
<br>
I guess what i meant by 'greening out' was that it's not nearly the target rich area it was at 25/26/27/28.   I got most of those levels in Llyn Barfog solo or with a partner.   It's so-so exp solo and not worth it for any group that can take the bigger ones.<br>
<br>
I'm just finding the whole Midgard experience to be much more kind than Albion has ever been.  I'll post a followup in a few days and see if the experience holds true.<br>
<br>
