<br>
No, I think you haven't been looking in the right areas.  Look at my crude map, shamelessly ripped from daatlas.com:<br>
<br>
<img src=http://www.geocities.com/lag999/barfog.txt><br>
<br>
In the circle marked "A" is a bwgan camp that has about 6 to 8 lake-side fishermen spawns and 4 spawns (3 linked) a bit further in, including a level 30 quest NPC named Ifor.  If you're soloing as a friar, stick to the lakeside spawns which are not linked for the most part.  (You'd swear they were linked by their proximity to one another, but only very rarely will even two be linked.)  The fishermen in this camp are levels 26 to 31, considerably higher than the low 20s bwgan you see wandering elsewhere, such as the few that normally walk the coastline.  They are also physically bigger.  If you feel comfortable handling 4 at a time, you can also pull the Ifor camp.  Altogether you have a ton of great NPC spawns in a small area.<br>
<br>
Now just up the hill from spot A, the oval I marked as "B", is an area where bwgwl spawn.  You really shouldn't need to go here if you're soloing, but if you're sharing the bwgan area, consider it.  A minimum of 6 high 20s bwgwl spawn in this area, usually walking near the edge of the hill.  Very often they will be linked, though, even in groups of 3.<br>
<br>
Now at approximately "C" is the undead fort containing the low 30s undead.  This area is usually camped more than the others, but with some sort of crowd control you're in business.  And sorcerers are attracted to Llyn Barfog because the bwgan camp is one of the few excellent soloing spots for soloing sorcerers.  Easy, reliable experience. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxzzy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xzzy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/28/01 12:34:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I sampled the dark side</span><hr size=1> > All the mobs seemed drop more loot than Albion and the loot they did have seemed to sell for about <br>
