Minor Update here.<br>
<br>
I got home tonight and finally found Rana the Healer trainer.  I was looking for her last night when I went to bed.<br>
<br>
All I gotta say is SHEESH.<br>
<br>
Now granted, I checked out what Mid Healers get, but @#$%.<br>
<br>
I hadn't trained anything until 5 and at 5, I went 5 points into augmentation since I wanted the run buff.<br>
<br>
So, I spent half an hour killing greenies testing out spells and stuff.<br>
<br>
My healer gets:<br>
<br>
AF buff<br>
Haste Buff<br>
STR buff<br>
CON buff<br>
<br>
He gets a free dmg add.  Similar to what thurgs and wizards get, but this one is a conc based so costs no additional mana.<br>
<br>
Free Run speed like a minstrel<br>
<br>
The best heals and some instant ones later on.<br>
<br>
Single target stun.  AOE Stun.   Single Target mez and hatelist management.<br>
<br>
This guy is a chain wearing Minstrel/Theurg/Cleric all rolled up into one.   The only lack is the weapon, but with the bonus dmg, that helps things a ton.<br>
<br>
I guess it's just disgusting me.<br>
<br>
My friar gets a haste line.   Once that costs power constantly and would last 2-3 minutes tops at 29...not a permanent buff.  It also doesn't stack with his End buff that also costs power constantly.<br>
<br>
This guy gets chain, my friar gets leather.   Friar's are a 2h class, this healer gets a shield.<br>
While friars can SORTA use a shield, the only one they can equip is the starter shield.  It's still bugged, even though they are supposed to be able to use a shield.  The weapon would be useless since friars can't train a 1h.   Friars have no range spells.   Healers do.<br>
<br>
To top all this off....the healer gets a power regen spell!!  SHEESH.<br>
<br>
crowd control, best buffs, best healing, range attacks and chain armor.   No doubt about it...Mid Healers are the closest thing to a tank mage going.<br>
<br>
Grr.   I can't believe how gimped friars are.   Sure, my friar can dish damage...he just can't take it.  If I use my best styles, they are higher aggro even if less damage than an Armsman.  I think someone got beat up by Monks as a child and took it out on Friars in this game.<br>
<br>
<br>
